== Misc ==



  * Executable files under Human68k or SX-Windows have the .X extension.  They are run by typing the filename at the command prompt, minus the .X extension, or double-clicking the file icon in SX-Windows.



  * Many basic DOS functions are also present under Human68k, like dir, tree, copy, even pushing <key>F3</key> (not <key>XF3</key>) to re-display the last command.



  * Don't know how to type in Japanese filenames?  Under Human68k, you can push <key>Tab</key> to cycle through file or directory names in the current directory.  It can also complete file or directory names for you, if you have already typed the first few characters.



  * Most game disks are bootable, so generally no interaction with Human68k is needed for them.



== Keyboard ==



This system requires full keyboard emulation to work correctly. At startup, full keyboard emulation mode is enabled by default. Whilst in full keyboard emulation mode, some key associated functionality may be disabled (like the <key>Esc</key> key for EXIT). The keyboard emulation mode is toggled using the <key>ScrollLock</key> key (by default).



